Key takeaways:
- Patterns present: MVC/Web API controllers, constructor-based DI, EF Core Unit of Work via `SmartCityContext`, and optimistic concurrency with `RowVersion`.
- Gaps: no repository/service abstractions; no Factory/Strategy/Observer; controllers tightly coupled to EF `DbSet`s.
- Abstract vs concrete: only framework abstractions (`DbContext`, `ControllerBase`, etc.); project code is all concrete (8 controllers, 12 entities, 1 DbContext); no custom interfaces.
- Decoupling/SOLID grade: C+ (good SRP/DI and transactions; weaker testability and layering).
- Pattern density: 4 patterns across 21 classes → 0.19.

